1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,192 --> 00:01:37,688
=Episode 30=
(Things Only a Mother Can Do)

3
00:02:19,540 --> 00:02:20,540
What are you doing here?

4
00:02:21,339 --> 00:02:22,899
Wenjun, please.

5
00:02:23,459 --> 00:02:24,700
Give this to Bai Shu.

6
00:02:25,499 --> 00:02:26,540
Tell her it's okay now.

7
00:02:27,179 --> 00:02:27,980
What happened?

8
00:02:28,939 --> 00:02:29,944
You don't need to know.

9
00:02:30,980 --> 00:02:31,820
It's all settled.

10
00:02:35,499 --> 00:02:36,659
Wenjun, take this.

11
00:02:52,339 --> 00:02:53,580
Zhou Yun's pen?

12
00:02:54,659 --> 00:02:55,899
How did she get it?

13
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:39,820
How long has this farm been shut down?

14
00:03:41,059 --> 00:03:41,820
Half a year.

15
00:03:43,860 --> 00:03:47,059
You've been living here for half a year?

16
00:03:48,580 --> 00:03:49,880
Water and electricity available.

17
00:03:50,020 --> 00:03:51,339
What do you live on?

18
00:03:52,300 --> 00:03:54,100
The boss couldn't move a few deer.

19
00:03:54,540 --> 00:03:55,899
So he asked me to look after them.

20
00:03:56,459 --> 00:03:57,540
He pays me some money.

21
00:03:58,179 --> 00:04:00,580
They'll build a second floor out back
and run a farm stay.

22
00:04:00,739 --> 00:04:02,140
I eat with the workers.

23
00:04:04,260 --> 00:04:05,219
A site here?

24
00:04:07,659 --> 00:04:09,339
Why don't I hear any construction noise?

25
00:04:10,339 --> 00:04:12,140
This morning, the power went out.

26
00:04:13,700 --> 00:04:14,820
Workers took half a day off

27
00:04:15,179 --> 00:04:16,500
and went into town for a bath.

28
00:04:24,940 --> 00:04:27,260
Those things you said to me
outside my home.

29
00:04:28,779 --> 00:04:29,740
What did you mean?

30
00:04:34,299 --> 00:04:35,099
Tell me.

31
00:04:37,659 --> 00:04:39,740
Has Bai Shu gotten
into some kind of trouble?

32
00:04:42,899 --> 00:04:44,099
Just tell me.

33
00:04:46,060 --> 00:04:47,500
I have more connections than you do.

34
00:04:52,979 --> 00:04:54,020
Tell me.

35
00:05:31,620 --> 00:05:32,539
Wenjun,

36
00:05:38,539 --> 00:05:40,659
this is her bag.

37
00:05:41,339 --> 00:05:42,979
I was going to turn myself in with it.

38
00:05:44,539 --> 00:05:47,020
I killed her. It has nothing
to do with Bai Shu.

39
00:05:48,260 --> 00:05:49,380
I washed the pen.

40
00:05:50,899 --> 00:05:52,140
I used to hear

41
00:05:52,899 --> 00:05:55,219
that covering blood with more blood
could fool the police.

42
00:06:02,580 --> 00:06:03,380
Tell me.

43
00:06:06,580 --> 00:06:07,940
Where is Zhou Na's body?

44
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:11,140
I won't

45
00:06:13,020 --> 00:06:13,859
tell you this.

46
00:06:16,779 --> 00:06:18,180
I'll only tell the police.

47
00:06:20,299 --> 00:06:22,580
Only then can I prove
I'm the real killer.

48
00:06:28,419 --> 00:06:29,700
Tell me.

49
00:06:30,859 --> 00:06:31,820
Just tell me!

50
00:06:33,539 --> 00:06:34,700
I can figure something out.

51
00:06:35,459 --> 00:06:36,299
Wenjun,

52
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:43,539
I won't tell you.

53
00:06:46,380 --> 00:06:47,659
I gave birth to her.

54
00:06:49,820 --> 00:06:51,260
I'm her birth mother.

55
00:06:51,940 --> 00:06:52,779
(You're her mother?)

56
00:06:52,779 --> 00:06:53,940
Since she got into trouble,

57
00:06:54,859 --> 00:06:56,180
I have to take the blame for her.

58
00:06:56,180 --> 00:06:57,180
(Then who am I?)

59
00:06:58,140 --> 00:06:58,899
Stay out of it.

60
00:06:59,899 --> 00:07:01,260
(Stay out of it?)

61
00:07:01,659 --> 00:07:02,580
You should leave now.

62
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:08,299
I warned you not to see Bai Shu again.

63
00:07:08,580 --> 00:07:09,740
You lied to me again.

64
00:07:10,820 --> 00:07:12,580
You're all lying to me.

65
00:07:15,020 --> 00:07:16,299
As long as you're around,

66
00:07:16,940 --> 00:07:19,539
things will never be right
between me and Bai Shu.

67
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:24,299
She's my daughter.

68
00:07:25,219 --> 00:07:27,339
I've never done anything for her
in my whole life.

69
00:07:29,659 --> 00:07:33,180
(You did. You abandoned her.)

70
00:07:34,339 --> 00:07:36,140
(Now you come to play the hero now?)

71
00:07:37,140 --> 00:07:39,260
(I raised her all by myself.)

72
00:07:40,380 --> 00:07:42,099
(I'm her mother.)

73
00:07:42,779 --> 00:07:45,180
This is the only thing I can do for her.

74
00:07:55,700 --> 00:07:57,260
Don't you want to see Bai Shu?

75
00:07:59,859 --> 00:08:00,820
Can I see her?

76
00:08:03,419 --> 00:08:05,020
I dream of seeing her.

77
00:08:06,339 --> 00:08:07,740
I want so to hug her

78
00:08:08,779 --> 00:08:09,700
and kiss her badly.

79
00:08:12,099 --> 00:08:13,060
All these years,

80
00:08:15,020 --> 00:08:17,180
- (I also want to hug her)
- I could only ever

81
00:08:17,459 --> 00:08:19,060
- (and kiss her.)
- watch her from afar.

82
00:08:19,859 --> 00:08:20,859
(But all these years...)

83
00:08:21,020 --> 00:08:22,060
I secretly followed you.

84
00:08:22,060 --> 00:08:24,260
(She wouldn't even call me Mom.)

85
00:08:25,779 --> 00:08:27,940
I wanted to hug my daughter so badly.

86
00:08:34,779 --> 00:08:35,500
Wenjun.

87
00:08:42,860 --> 00:08:44,460
I'll arrange for you to meet.

88
00:08:47,620 --> 00:08:49,020
Before you go to jail,

89
00:08:52,699 --> 00:08:53,740
I will definitely

90
00:08:55,539 --> 00:08:57,699
make her call you

91
00:09:03,539 --> 00:09:04,460
Mom.

92
00:09:05,059 --> 00:09:08,579
I told you to say "Mom, I'm sorry!"

93
00:09:13,020 --> 00:09:15,020
Hurt me!

94
00:09:16,860 --> 00:09:18,659
Can you find a better mother than me?

95
00:09:57,380 --> 00:10:00,140
Mom!

96
00:10:19,380 --> 00:10:21,100
I've told you many times.

97
00:10:22,779 --> 00:10:24,579
And you've promised me countless times

98
00:10:25,539 --> 00:10:26,579
that you would leave.

99
00:10:28,500 --> 00:10:29,419
You lied.

100
00:10:34,579 --> 00:10:35,419
All these years,

101
00:10:36,659 --> 00:10:39,260
out of respect for you
also being a mother,

102
00:10:40,939 --> 00:10:42,419
I've always been putting up with you.

103
00:10:43,659 --> 00:10:45,460
But how did you repay me?

104
00:10:49,899 --> 00:10:51,579
You stalked my child.

105
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:54,340
You tried to get close to her.

106
00:10:56,860 --> 00:10:58,659
Do you think I don't know
what's on your mind?

107
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:02,059
You know

108
00:11:03,340 --> 00:11:05,100
you're her birth mother.

109
00:11:06,419 --> 00:11:09,819
You know you're irreplaceable.

110
00:11:13,380 --> 00:11:14,579
So you bully me

111
00:11:15,980 --> 00:11:17,100
and manipulate me.

112
00:11:19,860 --> 00:11:21,500
Just because you gave birth to her,

113
00:11:22,419 --> 00:11:24,579
you haunt and threaten me endlessly.

114
00:11:32,020 --> 00:11:32,939
You deserve it.

115
00:11:55,500 --> 00:11:57,460
Didn't you want to give Bai Shu freedom?

116
00:11:59,140 --> 00:12:00,819
Her freedom isn't yours to give.

117
00:12:01,740 --> 00:12:02,740
You're not worthy.

118
00:12:38,179 --> 00:12:38,939
Hello?

119
00:12:40,500 --> 00:12:43,740
Zhao, if someone illegally builds
on forest land,

120
00:12:43,740 --> 00:12:44,659
what should we do?

121
00:12:44,939 --> 00:12:47,340
When I arrived, I saw
leftover cement on the ground.

122
00:12:49,020 --> 00:12:49,539
Shutdown.

123
00:12:50,539 --> 00:12:52,579
Okay, I'll send you the location later.

124
00:12:52,579 --> 00:12:54,500
Okay.

125
00:13:00,220 --> 00:13:01,579
Hello, Mr. Liu?

126
00:13:02,260 --> 00:13:05,419
Do you have a concrete cutter
at your construction site?

127
00:13:06,860 --> 00:13:07,539
Lend it to me.

128
00:13:08,460 --> 00:13:09,340
Find me two workers

129
00:13:10,579 --> 00:13:11,579
and a truck.

130
00:13:14,179 --> 00:13:14,776
Okay.

131
00:13:45,496 --> 00:13:47,224
(Huang Zhiqiang)

132
00:13:52,819 --> 00:13:53,419
Hello?

133
00:13:55,179 --> 00:13:56,220
Bai Shu's in trouble.

134
00:13:58,899 --> 00:14:00,740
Bai Shu and Ren Xiaoming killed someone.

135
00:14:04,659 --> 00:14:06,539
I've already taken care of the body
for them.

136
00:14:07,860 --> 00:14:09,100
But it's not foolproof yet.

137
00:14:11,659 --> 00:14:13,460
I need you to do something for Bai Shu.

138
00:14:14,860 --> 00:14:16,460
Come ten hours later.

139
00:14:28,500 --> 00:14:29,179
Where's Zhou Na?

140
00:14:30,059 --> 00:14:31,500
Find a spot at your site.

141
00:14:33,740 --> 00:14:34,460
Seal it up.

142
00:14:42,968 --> 00:14:43,860
(Qidaohezi, 2023)
So

143
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:47,380
you didn't know
where Zhou Na's body is either?

144
00:14:48,380 --> 00:14:49,620
Ge Wenjun didn't know either.

145
00:14:50,699 --> 00:14:53,819
Only Zhang Cuiping knew.

146
00:14:55,939 --> 00:14:57,340
You faked testimony for Ge Wenjun

147
00:14:57,980 --> 00:15:00,819
to prevent Bai Shu from learning
the victim's true identity,

148
00:15:01,740 --> 00:15:02,328
right?

149
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:10,860
Imagine if Bai Shu knew

150
00:15:11,860 --> 00:15:13,699
that the victim was her birth mother,

151
00:15:14,939 --> 00:15:16,260
how heartbroken would she be?

152
00:15:28,860 --> 00:15:29,659
Kill me,

153
00:15:31,100 --> 00:15:33,020
and Bai Shu will be beyond saving.

154
00:15:51,899 --> 00:15:52,740
Now,

155
00:15:54,380 --> 00:15:57,980
the police confirmed
the body in the cement is Zhou Na.

156
00:15:58,899 --> 00:16:02,260
Bai Shu and Ren Xiaoming
will race to confess.

157
00:16:03,179 --> 00:16:06,779
But neither of them knows
how she actually died.

158
00:16:09,539 --> 00:16:12,620
If you want them
completely cleared of this,

159
00:16:15,220 --> 00:16:16,819
I have the perfect solution.

160
00:16:18,419 --> 00:16:21,220
I can give you airtight testimony,

161
00:16:22,620 --> 00:16:24,500
proving neither of them is the murderer,

162
00:16:25,220 --> 00:16:28,220
and you are the real killer.

163
00:16:43,740 --> 00:16:47,860
If you truly care
about Bai Shu, listen to me.

164
00:16:51,579 --> 00:16:52,779
She won't go to prison,

165
00:16:53,340 --> 00:16:56,299
and she'll never know
the victim is her mother.

166
00:16:59,260 --> 00:17:01,460
She'll live happily
for the rest of her life.

167
00:17:04,539 --> 00:17:06,819
Isn't this exactly what you wanted?

168
00:17:17,460 --> 00:17:19,859
So that confession you gave the police

169
00:17:20,020 --> 00:17:21,180
was all taught by Ge Wenjun?

170
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:24,152
Yeah.

171
00:17:26,059 --> 00:17:28,020
She told me the testimony

172
00:17:29,539 --> 00:17:32,180
just seconds
before I entered the station.

173
00:17:39,460 --> 00:17:41,420
You've already
asked Zhang Fang to confess.

174
00:17:41,940 --> 00:17:44,180
He'll hide
the victim's identity for you.

175
00:17:46,020 --> 00:17:46,700
Why?

176
00:17:47,460 --> 00:17:50,180
Why reveal the truth to me like this?

177
00:17:52,859 --> 00:17:54,059
I'm getting revenge on you

178
00:17:57,660 --> 00:18:00,379
for all these years
of cold indifference.

179
00:18:04,700 --> 00:18:06,700
I gave you all my love,

180
00:18:08,539 --> 00:18:09,379
yet you rejected it

181
00:18:10,779 --> 00:18:12,420
and even trampled it underfoot.

182
00:18:20,020 --> 00:18:21,539
I don't love you anymore.

183
00:18:24,579 --> 00:18:25,500
I hate you.

184
00:18:30,379 --> 00:18:32,619
But these people are innocent.

185
00:18:33,539 --> 00:18:34,420
Innocent?

186
00:18:35,900 --> 00:18:38,180
Ren Xiaoming, Zhang Fang,

187
00:18:38,819 --> 00:18:40,740
and my birth mother.

188
00:18:42,260 --> 00:18:44,539
They are all innocent.

189
00:18:46,859 --> 00:18:48,180
Is Zhang Cuiping innocent?

190
00:18:49,059 --> 00:18:50,859
How could she abandon you back then

191
00:18:51,940 --> 00:18:53,500
and return now to play the saint?

192
00:18:54,379 --> 00:18:55,500
Innocent?

193
00:19:07,059 --> 00:19:10,220
I handled it for you. It's over.

194
00:19:12,900 --> 00:19:15,579
Isn't that what I should say
as your mother?

195
00:19:18,339 --> 00:19:19,539
Innocent?

196
00:19:21,420 --> 00:19:23,619
A woman who abandoned her own child

197
00:19:25,099 --> 00:19:26,500
deserves to die.

198
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:33,779
Everyone I punished

199
00:19:35,660 --> 00:19:37,099
is guilty without exception.

200
00:19:38,420 --> 00:19:41,859
I'd never harm anyone without fault.

201
00:19:43,700 --> 00:19:47,619
But knowing this won't help you.

202
00:19:48,460 --> 00:19:50,180
You'll never find Zhou Na,

203
00:19:50,819 --> 00:19:52,180
nor will you find Xiaoyu.

204
00:19:57,020 --> 00:19:58,700
Grandma, what are you doing?

205
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:00,700
Xiaoyu,

206
00:20:02,099 --> 00:20:03,619
I'm talking to your mom.

207
00:20:03,619 --> 00:20:04,379
Xiaoyu.

208
00:20:05,220 --> 00:20:07,260
Mom, where are you?

209
00:20:07,379 --> 00:20:08,660
Come find us quickly.

210
00:20:12,139 --> 00:20:13,500
- Xiaoyu,
- Where's Xiaoyu?

211
00:20:13,579 --> 00:20:14,539
tell your mom,

212
00:20:15,180 --> 00:20:18,779
"Mom, I miss you."

213
00:20:19,099 --> 00:20:21,260
Mom, I miss you.

214
00:20:22,180 --> 00:20:23,379
Where's Xiaoyu?

215
00:20:25,619 --> 00:20:27,460
Our Xiaoyu is such a good girl.

216
00:20:52,420 --> 00:20:54,180
Xiaoming! Xiaoming!

217
00:20:54,579 --> 00:20:55,579
Don't sleep here.

218
00:20:55,980 --> 00:20:57,779
Listen. How strong
your heart is beating.

219
00:21:01,048 --> 00:21:05,464
(Qidaohezi, 2010)

220
00:21:14,339 --> 00:21:15,579
Why are you all dressed up?

221
00:21:15,700 --> 00:21:16,500
What are you doing?

222
00:21:16,539 --> 00:21:18,099
Your hair looks like a feather duster.

223
00:21:18,099 --> 00:21:19,579
(Friendship Eatery)
You look dizzy. Grab a drink tonight?

224
00:21:20,180 --> 00:21:21,099
Not drinking tonight.

225
00:21:23,180 --> 00:21:24,220
Alright, okay.

226
00:21:24,900 --> 00:21:27,539
(Friendship Eatery)
He Yuqiong, why are you dressed up?

227
00:21:27,700 --> 00:21:28,980
Did you make the Guo Bao Rou?

228
00:21:30,099 --> 00:21:30,859
Not yet.

229
00:21:31,859 --> 00:21:33,099
If you haven't, do it later.

230
00:21:33,144 --> 00:21:34,139
Tastes best fried fresh.

231
00:21:34,220 --> 00:21:35,139
Make it when I ask.

232
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:37,260
Got it, boss!

233
00:21:38,660 --> 00:21:39,859
That's what I like to hear.

234
00:21:39,859 --> 00:21:41,260
I'll really buy this shop later.

235
00:21:42,660 --> 00:21:44,299
You're going to buy my shop?

236
00:21:44,420 --> 00:21:45,460
That would be great.

237
00:21:45,740 --> 00:21:48,139
You pay me, and I'll work for you.

238
00:21:48,539 --> 00:21:49,660
I don't have to worry.

239
00:21:49,980 --> 00:21:51,460
Okay, it's settled then.

240
00:21:51,740 --> 00:21:52,980
I just withdrew 1,000.

241
00:21:53,819 --> 00:21:54,819
Take it as a deposit.

242
00:21:55,420 --> 00:21:57,420
You're not messing with me, are you?

243
00:21:57,579 --> 00:21:59,180
Why would I mess with you?

244
00:21:59,579 --> 00:22:01,980
I promise I'll buy your shop
within a year.

245
00:22:02,260 --> 00:22:03,900
But you have to save this table for me.

246
00:22:05,579 --> 00:22:06,539
I'll write you an IOU.

247
00:22:48,220 --> 00:22:50,500
How can someone your age
still carve words on the table?

248
00:22:50,660 --> 00:22:51,299
Look.

249
00:22:51,299 --> 00:22:53,859
A perfectly good table, ruined by you.

250
00:22:54,020 --> 00:22:55,260
I'm going to buy your shop.

251
00:22:55,260 --> 00:22:56,859
Why fuss over a table?

252
00:22:57,460 --> 00:22:59,779
No matter how old this table gets,
don't throw it away.

253
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:01,336
(Friendship Forever)

254
00:23:02,700 --> 00:23:03,379
Fire!

255
00:23:04,339 --> 00:23:05,500
There's a fire over there!

256
00:23:06,420 --> 00:23:07,819
The school bus is on fire!

257
00:23:08,260 --> 00:23:09,059
Fire!

258
00:23:09,304 --> 00:23:10,180
(Friendship Forever)

259
00:23:10,180 --> 00:23:11,059
What happened?

260
00:23:13,500 --> 00:23:14,579
What's on fire?

261
00:23:15,819 --> 00:23:17,379
There are kids inside!

262
00:23:17,940 --> 00:23:18,700
Hold this for me.

263
00:23:20,220 --> 00:23:21,460
Yuqiong, be careful!

264
00:23:24,139 --> 00:23:25,379
Put out the fire! Hurry!

265
00:23:25,740 --> 00:23:27,059
Go get water! Water!

266
00:23:28,740 --> 00:23:29,339
Faster!

267
00:23:31,779 --> 00:23:32,940
Open the door!

268
00:23:35,980 --> 00:23:37,220
Open the door!

269
00:23:37,220 --> 00:23:38,220
The door won't open.

270
00:23:39,020 --> 00:23:40,099
The driver passed out.

271
00:23:41,379 --> 00:23:42,379
Water's here!

272
00:24:05,500 --> 00:24:06,059
Catch the kid!

273
00:24:10,220 --> 00:24:11,059
Catch the kid!

274
00:24:11,180 --> 00:24:11,940
Be careful!

275
00:24:18,539 --> 00:24:19,260
Careful!

276
00:24:20,779 --> 00:24:21,700
Kid, come on!

277
00:24:23,420 --> 00:24:24,539
The driver fainted!

278
00:24:24,539 --> 00:24:25,460
Give me water!

279
00:24:39,139 --> 00:24:39,859
Sir, wake up!

280
00:24:40,059 --> 00:24:40,900
Sir, wake up now!

281
00:24:41,500 --> 00:24:42,579
Wake up, sir!

282
00:24:46,900 --> 00:24:47,480
Quick!

283
00:24:54,299 --> 00:24:55,819
There's still a kid inside!

284
00:25:42,339 --> 00:25:43,020
Over here!

285
00:25:43,859 --> 00:25:44,539
Take it slow.

286
00:25:45,859 --> 00:25:46,579
Hurry up!

287
00:25:46,740 --> 00:25:47,700
Catch her!

288
00:25:47,859 --> 00:25:48,900
Anyone else?

289
00:27:42,808 --> 00:27:50,744
(Friendship Forever)

290
00:27:53,099 --> 00:27:53,619
Let's go.

291
00:27:54,059 --> 00:27:54,859
Let's go back.

292
00:27:55,700 --> 00:27:56,579
Don't. It's dangerous.

293
00:27:56,819 --> 00:27:58,488
She has a gun. Let's go.

294
00:28:05,020 --> 00:28:06,299
Tiantian's gone.

295
00:28:27,339 --> 00:28:28,139
What happened?

296
00:29:08,152 --> 00:29:13,784
(Morgue)

297
00:29:19,700 --> 00:29:23,500
The new leather shoes.
Tiantian couldn't bear to wear them.

298
00:29:27,660 --> 00:29:28,980
Don't go in.

299
00:29:30,379 --> 00:29:31,460
Don't.

300
00:29:33,139 --> 00:29:34,819
Don't look.

301
00:29:46,900 --> 00:29:47,980
(Ren Xiaoming,)

302
00:29:48,859 --> 00:29:50,379
(get up now.)

303
00:29:51,379 --> 00:29:52,460
(Ren Xiaoming,)

304
00:29:53,500 --> 00:29:54,579
(do you miss me?)

305
00:29:55,900 --> 00:29:56,980
(Ren Xiaoming,)

306
00:29:58,299 --> 00:29:59,500
(get up now.)

307
00:30:00,619 --> 00:30:01,700
(Ren Xiaoming!)

308
00:30:02,579 --> 00:30:04,020
(Think of me, and you'll wake up.)

309
00:30:05,980 --> 00:30:06,980
What are you doing?

310
00:30:07,579 --> 00:30:08,260
Come chase me.

311
00:30:08,260 --> 00:30:09,619
What are you doing?

312
00:30:10,740 --> 00:30:11,700
- Don't run.
- Ren Xiaoming,

313
00:30:13,059 --> 00:30:14,420
come catch me.

314
00:30:14,980 --> 00:30:16,700
Come catch me, Ren Xiaoming.

315
00:30:18,059 --> 00:30:19,339
Look at you. You're laughing.

316
00:30:20,299 --> 00:30:21,460
Go back.

317
00:30:21,779 --> 00:30:23,819
You couldn't go
where I used to want to go.

318
00:30:24,779 --> 00:30:27,299
You can't go
where I want to go now either.

319
00:30:28,099 --> 00:30:28,859
Go back.

320
00:30:30,859 --> 00:30:31,740
Go back.

321
00:30:32,619 --> 00:30:33,460
Go back!

322
00:30:34,900 --> 00:30:35,900
Go back!

323
00:30:36,819 --> 00:30:38,539
Go back, Ren Xiaoming!

324
00:30:39,700 --> 00:30:41,260
He Yuqiong!

325
00:30:41,940 --> 00:30:43,859
Ren Xiaoming, go back!

326
00:30:45,020 --> 00:30:47,619
Don't go.

327
00:30:48,099 --> 00:30:48,660
Wait for me.

328
00:30:48,859 --> 00:30:50,660
(Xiaoming. Xiaoming.)

329
00:30:51,020 --> 00:30:52,099
(Don't sleep.)

330
00:30:52,220 --> 00:30:54,099
(Listen. How strong
your heart is beating.)

331
00:30:54,260 --> 00:30:55,260
(Get up.)

332
00:30:55,339 --> 00:30:56,420
He Yuqiong!

333
00:31:08,220 --> 00:31:09,059
You're awake.

334
00:31:09,700 --> 00:31:10,500
Why did you come?

335
00:31:12,779 --> 00:31:14,139
Raise the bed a bit.

336
00:31:14,700 --> 00:31:15,980
You can't move now.

337
00:31:16,500 --> 00:31:18,539
I feel uncomfortable. I can't breathe.

338
00:31:26,500 --> 00:31:28,579
Don't worry. Your neck is fine.

339
00:31:31,940 --> 00:31:33,460
Don't move.

340
00:31:35,420 --> 00:31:37,180
Your foot is swollen like a big radish.

341
00:31:37,779 --> 00:31:40,420
As long as my brain isn't a radish,
I'm fine.

342
00:31:41,859 --> 00:31:43,379
The child is okay.

343
00:31:44,220 --> 00:31:45,740
Falling from such a height,

344
00:31:45,980 --> 00:31:48,099
you survived, because he wanted to live.

345
00:31:48,500 --> 00:31:50,379
You're lucky to be with the child.

346
00:31:50,700 --> 00:31:52,740
Don't give me this feudal superstition.

347
00:31:53,779 --> 00:31:55,339
I didn't even plan to keep this child.

348
00:31:56,220 --> 00:31:57,139
Silly girl.

349
00:31:57,379 --> 00:31:59,020
Your child just saved your life.

350
00:31:59,139 --> 00:32:01,379
I'm getting a divorce.
Why would I want this child?

351
00:32:01,619 --> 00:32:03,020
Decide for yourself.

352
00:32:05,460 --> 00:32:06,579
Can I care for you always?

353
00:32:07,180 --> 00:32:08,619
If I'm gone one day,

354
00:32:09,180 --> 00:32:10,619
things will still be as they should.

355
00:32:11,500 --> 00:32:12,779
I knew you'd say that.

356
00:32:13,099 --> 00:32:14,139
Do you parents

357
00:32:14,139 --> 00:32:16,579
only say these things to manipulate us?

358
00:32:16,779 --> 00:32:17,779
Is there any other trick?

359
00:32:23,740 --> 00:32:24,500
Your hand?

360
00:32:24,660 --> 00:32:25,339
I'm okay.

361
00:32:25,700 --> 00:32:26,500
Don't move.

362
00:32:26,500 --> 00:32:27,020
Let me see.

363
00:32:27,220 --> 00:32:27,859
Don't move.

364
00:32:27,900 --> 00:32:28,980
- What's wrong?
- Don't move.

365
00:32:29,339 --> 00:32:30,260
Are you unwell?

366
00:32:31,379 --> 00:32:32,460
There's something I've been

367
00:32:33,539 --> 00:32:34,700
wanting to tell you.

368
00:32:36,180 --> 00:32:36,940
Xiaoming...

369
00:32:40,099 --> 00:32:41,379
Visitors for Bed Two.

370
00:32:42,460 --> 00:32:45,099
Xiaoming, what's wrong with you?

371
00:32:45,379 --> 00:32:46,379
Why are you hospitalized?

372
00:32:46,619 --> 00:32:47,859
Who are you?

373
00:32:48,660 --> 00:32:49,379
Your neck...

374
00:32:49,579 --> 00:32:50,539
How did this happen?

375
00:32:50,539 --> 00:32:51,539
Who are you looking for?

376
00:32:51,539 --> 00:32:52,180
I'm fine.

377
00:32:52,819 --> 00:32:54,099
They are Liu Xiaoran's parents.

378
00:32:54,980 --> 00:32:55,740
I'm fine.

379
00:32:55,740 --> 00:32:56,779
Why did you come over?

380
00:32:57,420 --> 00:32:59,660
Well, our hands are dirty.

381
00:32:59,660 --> 00:33:00,420
- We'll go wash up.
- Wash up.

382
00:33:00,779 --> 00:33:01,900
- The washroom is there.
- Okay.

383
00:33:01,900 --> 00:33:02,700
Come on.

384
00:33:02,900 --> 00:33:03,460
Wash hands.

385
00:33:07,500 --> 00:33:09,779
Did I even forget Xiaoran's parents?

386
00:33:17,940 --> 00:33:19,299
We had dinner together years ago.

387
00:33:19,460 --> 00:33:20,420
Look, it's not them.

388
00:33:20,420 --> 00:33:21,020
I know.

389
00:33:21,020 --> 00:33:21,660
It's these two.

390
00:33:21,660 --> 00:33:24,299
I know. They're actors he hired.

391
00:33:24,660 --> 00:33:25,619
Fake.

392
00:33:26,579 --> 00:33:27,700
Those two are the real ones.

393
00:33:29,339 --> 00:33:31,020
(Even parents can be faked.)

394
00:33:34,859 --> 00:33:38,180
We haven't seen each other
in so many years.

395
00:33:38,900 --> 00:33:40,980
This is Zhuodi's dad.

396
00:33:41,740 --> 00:33:42,980
I'm Zhuodi's mom.

397
00:33:44,420 --> 00:33:47,139
Who is Zhuodi?

398
00:33:47,260 --> 00:33:49,379
Zhuodi is our son,

399
00:33:49,779 --> 00:33:50,859
your son-in-law.

400
00:33:51,099 --> 00:33:53,660
Yes, Zhuodi is our son.

401
00:33:55,384 --> 00:33:56,579
Well, Xiaoming.

402
00:33:56,619 --> 00:33:57,619
Some good stuff for you.

403
00:34:01,619 --> 00:34:03,740
Zhuodi is Liu Xiaoran's real name.

404
00:34:03,980 --> 00:34:05,020
I'll tell you later.

405
00:34:05,460 --> 00:34:07,099
Really kind of look like Xiaoran.

406
00:34:08,099 --> 00:34:09,619
Look, these dates

407
00:34:09,900 --> 00:34:11,780
were picked from our own trees.

408
00:34:12,460 --> 00:34:14,139
- These are walnuts.
- Thank you.

409
00:34:14,139 --> 00:34:14,940
- These are walnuts.
- Thank you.

410
00:34:15,259 --> 00:34:16,940
- Thank you.
- Eat dates to replenish your blood.

411
00:34:17,179 --> 00:34:17,780
Apples.

412
00:34:18,020 --> 00:34:18,900
So many.

413
00:34:20,460 --> 00:34:21,579
You should eat more fruit.

414
00:34:21,820 --> 00:34:22,659
The king of fruits.

415
00:34:22,900 --> 00:34:23,699
Thank you.

416
00:34:23,900 --> 00:34:24,940
Eat more. It's nutritious.

417
00:34:25,219 --> 00:34:27,139
Take good care of yourself
during pregnancy.

418
00:34:27,340 --> 00:34:28,820
Have the baby safely.

419
00:34:29,940 --> 00:34:31,139
We're both in good health.

420
00:34:31,420 --> 00:34:32,940
We'll help with the baby. Don't worry.

421
00:34:33,340 --> 00:34:36,099
We'll definitely make sure
the baby grows healthy and strong.

422
00:34:36,340 --> 00:34:37,020
Keep the baby.

423
00:34:37,659 --> 00:34:39,739
Carry on the Liu family line.

424
00:34:39,780 --> 00:34:40,659
Thank you so much.

425
00:34:41,020 --> 00:34:41,820
What are you doing?

426
00:34:41,820 --> 00:34:42,380
Keep the baby.

427
00:34:42,380 --> 00:34:42,980
Thank you.

428
00:34:43,179 --> 00:34:43,900
Did you hear me?

429
00:34:44,099 --> 00:34:44,699
Keep the baby.

430
00:34:45,900 --> 00:34:46,579
Ren Xiaoming.

431
00:34:47,020 --> 00:34:48,099
Who are you?

432
00:34:48,099 --> 00:34:48,820
Who are you?

433
00:34:48,820 --> 00:34:49,420
Get out!

434
00:34:49,420 --> 00:34:50,059
Get out now!

435
00:34:50,179 --> 00:34:50,820
Out!

436
00:34:51,059 --> 00:34:51,780
Get out!

437
00:34:52,980 --> 00:34:54,059
What's going on here?

438
00:34:58,980 --> 00:34:59,659
Okay.

439
00:35:03,820 --> 00:35:04,579
Thanks, sir.

440
00:35:04,940 --> 00:35:05,699
Thanks, sir.

441
00:35:08,420 --> 00:35:11,300
Liu Zhaodi is his real name.

442
00:35:11,460 --> 00:35:14,500
Liu Zhuodi is Liu Xiaoran's real name.

443
00:35:14,980 --> 00:35:17,219
He thought his name was tacky
after high school,

444
00:35:17,460 --> 00:35:19,020
so he changed it at the police station.

445
00:35:19,780 --> 00:35:20,619
Then at university,

446
00:35:21,099 --> 00:35:24,059
he was afraid classmates would think
his family was poor,

447
00:35:24,340 --> 00:35:26,380
and looked down on him
for being unsophisticated,

448
00:35:26,940 --> 00:35:28,500
so he faked a scholarly background.

449
00:35:28,860 --> 00:35:30,059
Once he started that lie,

450
00:35:31,059 --> 00:35:32,539
he could never tell the truth.

451
00:35:34,820 --> 00:35:36,300
When did you find out?

452
00:35:37,020 --> 00:35:38,820
I was fighting the divorce case
against him.

453
00:35:39,219 --> 00:35:40,699
So no matter the outcome,

454
00:35:41,300 --> 00:35:42,980
I felt I had to tell his parents.

455
00:35:43,780 --> 00:35:45,739
I dug up an old phone number,

456
00:35:46,219 --> 00:35:49,139
called it, and they didn't even know me.

457
00:35:50,739 --> 00:35:51,340
That's how

458
00:35:53,539 --> 00:35:54,659
I found out the truth.

459
00:35:55,259 --> 00:35:55,820
Oh, my!

460
00:35:57,579 --> 00:35:59,980
He told me the address on his ID card

461
00:36:00,539 --> 00:36:04,219
was where his grandfather's
ancestral tomb was.

462
00:36:04,340 --> 00:36:07,420
Said his parents registered hukou
in the village to remember their roots.

463
00:36:07,900 --> 00:36:09,659
But when I went to that address...

464
00:36:10,980 --> 00:36:12,099
Wait. Let me show you.

465
00:36:12,619 --> 00:36:13,500
Where's my phone?

466
00:36:15,820 --> 00:36:16,980
Is this yours?

467
00:36:17,900 --> 00:36:19,099
When I walked into the room,

468
00:36:20,699 --> 00:36:21,780
their family portrait

469
00:36:23,219 --> 00:36:24,300
was right in the center.

470
00:36:26,179 --> 00:36:28,059
He looked more and more like his dad.

471
00:36:29,699 --> 00:36:31,059
You showed him this photo?

472
00:36:31,259 --> 00:36:31,780
Yeah.

473
00:36:34,539 --> 00:36:36,659
How did he react
when you visited his parents?

474
00:36:36,820 --> 00:36:37,900
What do you think?

475
00:36:37,900 --> 00:36:40,340
Scared stiff, like he'd seen a ghost.

476
00:36:42,380 --> 00:36:43,780
How could he not be scared?

477
00:36:44,460 --> 00:36:46,739
He lives the high life all by himself,

478
00:36:47,699 --> 00:36:49,259
leaving his parents in the countryside.

479
00:36:50,139 --> 00:36:51,699
They're in their seventies or eighties,

480
00:36:52,420 --> 00:36:54,219
still farming to survive.

481
00:36:55,699 --> 00:36:56,940
He has no conscience.

482
00:36:58,940 --> 00:37:02,020
If this gets out,
public opinion will tear him apart.

483
00:37:05,179 --> 00:37:07,020
The people taking photos earlier
were media.

484
00:37:07,020 --> 00:37:07,579
Exactly.

485
00:37:11,020 --> 00:37:13,579
How did his parents find this place

486
00:37:14,900 --> 00:37:16,500
and know you're pregnant?

487
00:37:30,579 --> 00:37:31,900
Why not answer the phone?

488
00:37:32,900 --> 00:37:35,139
You fool, why not answer the phone?

489
00:37:37,420 --> 00:37:39,539
Chen Junhang, why not answer the phone?

490
00:37:39,940 --> 00:37:40,780
Where are you?

491
00:37:41,219 --> 00:37:43,219
Tell me the plan. Tell me!

492
00:37:56,920 --> 00:37:59,352
(Liu Xiaoran
Heartless Villain, Abandoned Parents)

493
00:38:00,780 --> 00:38:03,020
Fans sent it.
There are more in the company.

494
00:38:05,300 --> 00:38:07,099
Where's the plan?
What's the PR crisis plan?

495
00:38:07,259 --> 00:38:08,579
What PR?

496
00:38:08,739 --> 00:38:10,820
There's no PR to get you
out of this mess.

497
00:38:10,940 --> 00:38:11,659
No, what about...

498
00:38:16,420 --> 00:38:18,020
Junhang, what about the company?

499
00:38:18,219 --> 00:38:19,059
What's the stance?

500
00:38:19,219 --> 00:38:20,539
I need a way to handle this.

501
00:38:21,340 --> 00:38:21,940
It's handled.

502
00:38:23,980 --> 00:38:26,059
This is the result.

503
00:38:26,136 --> 00:38:26,776
(Release of Liability Contract)

504
00:38:28,340 --> 00:38:29,739
Look, sign them all.

505
00:38:29,739 --> 00:38:32,619
Amendment? Termination? Release?

506
00:38:32,699 --> 00:38:34,300
What does this mean?

507
00:38:34,940 --> 00:38:36,259
Are you kicking me out?

508
00:38:36,619 --> 00:38:37,739
Not my call.

509
00:38:38,259 --> 00:38:39,820
It's what the investors behind us want.

510
00:38:42,940 --> 00:38:43,900
You're joking?

511
00:38:44,099 --> 00:38:44,820
No.

512
00:38:46,659 --> 00:38:49,219
I won't sign them! I won't sign!

513
00:38:50,179 --> 00:38:51,300
If I sign, I'll...

514
00:38:51,300 --> 00:38:52,780
I'll have nothing left.

515
00:38:53,179 --> 00:38:55,500
If you don't sign,
then get ready to be sued.

516
00:38:57,739 --> 00:39:01,020
The shady stuff you did
has angered everyone.

517
00:39:01,860 --> 00:39:03,460
You've really set a record.

518
00:39:04,179 --> 00:39:05,860
Of all things to challenge,

519
00:39:06,099 --> 00:39:08,900
why did you have to pick thousands
of years of Chinese filial culture?

520
00:39:09,500 --> 00:39:11,980
You've ruined yourself, you know that?

521
00:39:25,340 --> 00:39:26,139
Junhang.

522
00:39:29,940 --> 00:39:30,860
Listen to me.

523
00:39:31,579 --> 00:39:33,539
Talk to them again.

524
00:39:33,780 --> 00:39:35,820
Talk to them again for me.

525
00:39:36,059 --> 00:39:36,940
Talk to them properly.

526
00:39:37,059 --> 00:39:39,059
I... I think there's a way around this.

527
00:39:39,059 --> 00:39:40,952
Look. It's negative buzz.

528
00:39:40,952 --> 00:39:42,259
But even negative buzz...

529
00:39:42,259 --> 00:39:43,500
It... It's still buzz, right?

530
00:39:43,500 --> 00:39:45,259
It... It has value, doesn't it?

531
00:39:45,259 --> 00:39:47,219
I have value too, right?

532
00:39:47,219 --> 00:39:47,940
- Like what?
- Well, like...

533
00:39:48,219 --> 00:39:51,460
Look, I could write a book
about this whole thing.

534
00:39:52,059 --> 00:39:53,059
That's a great idea.

535
00:39:53,340 --> 00:39:55,219
All your shady stuff
would definitely sell.

536
00:39:55,300 --> 00:39:56,020
I'll write it.

537
00:39:57,579 --> 00:39:58,539
You can't.

538
00:39:59,020 --> 00:39:59,659
I can.

539
00:39:59,739 --> 00:40:00,780
You can't write it.

540
00:40:00,860 --> 00:40:02,179
Why can't I?

541
00:40:02,659 --> 00:40:03,739
That thing you did...

542
00:40:03,900 --> 00:40:06,219
The plagiarism thing
is already common knowledge.

543
00:40:06,699 --> 00:40:08,980
What publisher would dare
put out your book now?

544
00:40:11,300 --> 00:40:13,739
Go talk to them. Look.

545
00:40:13,860 --> 00:40:15,219
They can't, but you can, right?

546
00:40:15,219 --> 00:40:16,860
You have such wide connections, right?

547
00:40:16,860 --> 00:40:18,659
With so many connections,
you must have a way.

548
00:40:18,659 --> 00:40:19,500
Let's cooperate.

549
00:40:19,579 --> 00:40:21,500
Then we can still eat steak together,

550
00:40:21,500 --> 00:40:23,059
and drink red wine, right?

551
00:40:23,139 --> 00:40:24,420
- You must have a way.
- Xiaoran.

552
00:40:24,619 --> 00:40:26,579
Xiaoran, save it.

553
00:40:27,099 --> 00:40:28,940
Just because we've cooperated for years,

554
00:40:29,460 --> 00:40:32,780
I'm advising you to be sensible
and sign them.

555
00:40:32,940 --> 00:40:35,340
Wouldn't it be nice to be
an ordinary person from now on?

556
00:40:35,860 --> 00:40:37,099
Sell this house,

557
00:40:37,300 --> 00:40:38,739
move to a smaller city,

558
00:40:39,020 --> 00:40:40,460
and you'll still live comfortably.

559
00:40:43,179 --> 00:40:45,820
But if you just refuse to let go,

560
00:40:46,980 --> 00:40:48,900
what awaits you
is massive compensation payments.

561
00:40:51,380 --> 00:40:53,219
Kick someone when they are down.

562
00:40:56,219 --> 00:40:57,300
You understand that, right?

563
00:40:58,300 --> 00:40:59,619
Alright, hurry up and sign.

564
00:41:00,340 --> 00:41:01,739
I have a lot to do this afternoon.

565
00:41:04,739 --> 00:41:06,820
Think back to when you won
all these awards,

566
00:41:07,460 --> 00:41:09,300
I was handling things around backstage.

567
00:41:10,099 --> 00:41:11,780
And you were on stage, putting on airs.

568
00:41:16,020 --> 00:41:20,340
I remember you thanked
your professor and your parents, right?

569
00:41:24,659 --> 00:41:26,860
You lied right in front
of the whole nation.

570
00:41:27,619 --> 00:41:28,780
Let me interview you.

571
00:41:29,420 --> 00:41:32,420
Aren't you ashamed?
Not even a little nervous?

572
00:41:32,900 --> 00:41:34,059
Don't you feel guilty?

573
00:41:35,980 --> 00:41:39,780
So your psychology
is truly something to admire.

574
00:41:43,860 --> 00:41:46,179
Alright, don't be ungrateful.

575
00:41:46,460 --> 00:41:48,579
You've enjoyed wealth and fame
all these years.

576
00:41:49,380 --> 00:41:52,059
With your background,
to have made it this far

577
00:41:52,659 --> 00:41:55,059
is like hitting the jackpot
for your ancestors.

578
00:41:57,539 --> 00:41:58,900
But regarding what you've done,

579
00:42:00,340 --> 00:42:01,780
even I feel angry hearing about it.

580
00:42:03,780 --> 00:42:07,340
I would never do something
as immoral as disowning my parents.

581
00:42:08,300 --> 00:42:11,300
Even your college classmates
didn't know your real background.

582
00:42:12,619 --> 00:42:14,460
You've lied for so many years.

583
00:42:15,099 --> 00:42:16,619
How did you manage it?

584
00:42:24,099 --> 00:42:26,179
Give me back what's mine!

585
00:42:27,340 --> 00:42:29,219
I won't allow you to disrespect me!

586
00:42:29,460 --> 00:42:32,300
I won't allow you
to look down on me and belittle me!

587
00:42:32,860 --> 00:42:34,500
Get up! Stop playing dead!

588
00:42:35,500 --> 00:42:37,699
Get up! Help me fix this!

589
00:42:37,860 --> 00:42:39,099
Smooth things over for me!

590
00:42:42,259 --> 00:42:43,179
Chen Junhang!

591
00:42:46,420 --> 00:42:47,059
I...

592
00:43:00,219 --> 00:43:00,980
Junhang...

593
00:43:05,000 --> 00:43:12,808
=Vanished Name=
